[ PONIES "AWW" ]

238
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:20,293
FINE.

239
00:09:20,327 --> 00:09:22,630
[ ALL CHEERING, LAUGHTER ]

240
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:30,003
FOOD'S ALL TAKEN CARE OF.
NEXT IS WEATHER.

241
00:09:30,037 --> 00:09:32,139
[ GROANS ]

242
00:09:32,172 --> 00:09:34,742
I ATE TOO MUCH PIE.

243
00:09:34,775 --> 00:09:35,876
HMM.

244
00:09:35,909 --> 00:09:38,646
THERE'S SUPPOSED TO BE A PEGASUS
PONY NAMED RAINBOW DASH

245
00:09:38,646 --> 00:09:39,780
CLEARING THE CLOUDS.

246
00:09:41,314 --> 00:09:44,151
WELL, SHE'S NOT DOING
A VERY GOOD JOB, IS SHE?

247
00:09:44,184 --> 00:09:45,686
[ ZOOM! ]

248
00:09:45,719 --> 00:09:47,655
[ GROANS ]

249
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:51,024
[ CHUCKLES ]

250
00:09:51,058 --> 00:09:53,126
UH, EXCUSE ME?

251
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,662
[ CHUCKLES ]

252
00:09:54,662 --> 00:09:55,663
MM.

253
00:09:55,663 --> 00:09:57,230
[ CHUCKLES ]
LET ME HELP YOU.

254
00:09:57,264 --> 00:09:58,866
[ ZIP! ]

255
00:09:58,899 --> 00:10:00,300
[ ZIP! ]

256
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:03,070
[ BOING! BOING! BOING! ]

257
00:10:05,673 --> 00:10:06,640
[ LAUGHS ]

258
00:10:06,674 --> 00:10:08,408
OOPS.
I GUESS I OVERDID IT.

259
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:11,011
UM, UH, HOW ABOUT THIS?

260
00:10:11,044 --> 00:10:15,348
MY VERY OWN PATENTED
RAINBLOW DRY.

261
00:10:15,382 --> 00:10:17,250
NO, NO.
DON'T THANK ME.

262
00:10:17,284 --> 00:10:18,852
YOU'RE QUITE WELCOME.

263
00:10:18,886 --> 00:10:19,853
UH --

264
00:10:19,887 --> 00:10:21,421
[ TING! ]

265
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:22,956
[ STIFLED LAUGH ]

266
00:10:22,990 --> 00:10:26,159
[ LAUGHS HYSTERICALLY ]

267
00:10:26,193 --> 00:10:28,028
[ LAUGHS ]

268
00:10:28,061 --> 00:10:31,098
LET ME GUESS --
YOU'RE RAINBOW DASH.

269
00:10:31,131 --> 00:10:32,866
THE ONE AND ONLY.

270
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:33,867
[ ZIP! ]

271
00:10:33,901 --> 00:10:35,202
WHY? YOU HEARD OF ME?

272
00:10:35,235 --> 00:10:38,038
I HEARD YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
KEEPING THE SKY CLEAR.

273
00:10:38,071 --> 00:10:39,306
[ SIGHS ]

274
00:10:39,339 --> 00:10:40,307
I'M TWILIGHT SPARKLE,

275
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:42,442
AND THE PRINCESS SENT ME
TO CHECK ON THE WEATHER.

276
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:44,444
YEAH, YEAH.
THAT'LL BE A SNAP.

277
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:45,879
I'LL DO IT IN A JIFFY,

278
00:10:45,913 --> 00:10:47,447
JUST AS SOON
AS I'M DONE PRACTICING.

279
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,149
PRACTICING? FOR WHAT?

280
00:10:49,182 --> 00:10:51,418
THE WONDERBOLTS.

281
00:10:51,451 --> 00:10:53,821
THEY'RE GONNA PERFORM
AT THE CELEBRATION TOMORROW,

282
00:10:53,854 --> 00:10:56,323
AND I'M GONNA SHOW THEM
MY STUFF.

283
00:10:56,356 --> 00:10:58,792
THE WONDERBOLTS?
YEP.

284
00:10:58,826 --> 00:11:01,962
THE MOST TALENTED FLIERS
IN ALL OF EQUESTRIA?

285
00:11:01,995 --> 00:11:03,030
THAT'S THEM.

286
00:11:03,063 --> 00:11:04,364
[ SCOFFS ] PLEASE.

287
00:11:04,397 --> 00:11:06,033
THEY'D NEVER ACCEPT
A PEGASUS

288
00:11:06,066 --> 00:11:08,736
WHO CAN'T EVEN KEEP THE SKY
CLEAR FOR ONE MEASLY DAY.

289
00:11:08,769 --> 00:11:12,439
HEY, I COULD CLEAR THIS SKY
IN 10 SECONDS FLAT.

290
00:11:12,472 --> 00:11:14,174
PROVE IT.

291
00:11:15,342 --> 00:11:17,444
[ ZIP! ]
[ GRUNTING ]

292
00:11:19,346 --> 00:11:20,948
[ WHOOSH! WHOOSH! ]

293
00:11:20,981 --> 00:11:24,351
HYAH!
LOOP THE LOOP AROUND AND WHAP!

294
00:11:24,384 --> 00:11:26,319
WHAT'D I SAY?

295
00:11:26,353 --> 00:11:28,922
10 SECONDS FLAT.

296
00:11:28,956 --> 00:11:31,324
I'D NEVER LEAVE
PONYVILLE HANGING.

297
00:11:31,358 --> 00:11:33,761
[ LAUGHS ]

298
00:11:33,794 --> 00:11:36,163
YOU SHOULD SEE
THE LOOK ON YOUR FACE.

299
00:11:36,196 --> 00:11:36,997
HA!

300
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:39,232
YOU'RE A LAUGH,
TWILIGHT SPARKLE.

301
00:11:39,266 --> 00:11:41,802
I CAN'T WAIT TO HANG OUT
SOME MORE.

302
00:11:41,835 --> 00:11:43,503
WOW!

303
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:47,407
SHE'S AMAZING!

304
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:50,110
[ LAUGHS ]
[ GROANS ]

305
00:11:50,143 --> 00:11:53,280
WAIT! IT'S KIND OF PRETTY
ONCE YOU GET USED TO IT.

306
00:11:55,783 --> 00:11:57,484
DECORATIONS.

307
00:11:57,517 --> 00:12:00,854
Spike: BEAUTIFUL!
Twilight Sparkle: YES.

308
00:12:00,888 --> 00:12:02,790
THE DECOR
IS COMING ALONG NICELY.

309
00:12:02,823 --> 00:12:03,957
THIS OUGHT TO BE QUICK.

310
00:12:03,991 --> 00:12:05,859
I'LL BE AT THE LIBRARY
IN NO TIME.

311
00:12:05,893 --> 00:12:07,427
BEAUTIFUL, INDEED.

312
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:10,130
NOT THE DECOR -- HER.

313
00:12:10,163 --> 00:12:12,165
NO, NO.

314
00:12:12,199 --> 00:12:13,166
NO.

315
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,968
OH, GOODNESS, NO.

316
00:12:15,002 --> 00:12:17,337
HOW ARE MY SPINES?
ARE THEY STRAIGHT?

317
00:12:17,370 --> 00:12:19,940
[ POP! POP! ]

318
00:12:19,973 --> 00:12:20,941
GOOD AFTERNOON.

319
00:12:20,974 --> 00:12:22,009
JUST A MOMENT, PLEASE.

320
00:12:22,042 --> 00:12:23,977
I'M IN THE ZONE,
AS IT WERE.

321
00:12:24,011 --> 00:12:25,378
OH, YES!

322
00:12:25,412 --> 00:12:28,081
SPARKLE ALWAYS DOES THE TRICK,
DOES IT NOT?

323
00:12:28,115 --> 00:12:30,150
WHY, RARITY,
YOU ARE A TALENT.

324
00:12:30,183 --> 00:12:33,821
NOW, UM, HOW CAN I HELP YOU --
AAH-HA-HA!

325
00:12:33,821 --> 00:12:36,089
OH, MY STARS, DARLING!

326
00:12:36,123 --> 00:12:38,191
WHATEVER HAPPENED
TO YOUR COIFFURE?

327
00:12:38,225 --> 00:12:40,393
OH, YOU MEAN MY MANE?

328
00:12:40,427 --> 00:12:41,829
WELL, IT'S A LONG STORY.

329
00:12:41,829 --> 00:12:43,396
I'M JUST HERE TO CHECK
ON THE DECORATIONS,

330
00:12:43,430 --> 00:12:44,965
AND THEN I'LL BE
OUT OF YOUR HAIR.

331
00:12:44,998 --> 00:12:46,199
OUT OF MY HAIR?

332
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:48,001
WHAT ABOUT YOUR HAIR?

333
00:12:48,035 --> 00:12:50,203
WAIT.
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

334
00:12:50,237 --> 00:12:51,471
HELP!

335
00:12:51,504 --> 00:12:53,440
[ WHIRL! WHIRL! ]

336
00:12:53,473 --> 00:12:56,009
Rarity:
NO. NO. UNH-UNH.

337
00:12:56,043 --> 00:12:57,945
TOO GREEN.
TOO YELLOW.

338
00:12:57,978 --> 00:12:59,847
TOO POOFY.
NOT POOFY ENOUGH.

339
00:12:59,847 --> 00:13:02,082
TOO FRILLY.
TOO SHINY.

340
00:13:02,115 --> 00:13:04,317
NOW GO ON, MY DEAR.

341
00:13:04,351 --> 00:13:06,519
YOU WERE TELLING ME
WHERE YOU'RE FROM.

342
00:13:06,553 --> 00:13:08,055
[ CREAKING ]

343
00:13:08,088 --> 00:13:09,389
I'VE...[GROANS]

344
00:13:09,422 --> 00:13:14,261
BEEN SENT...FROM CANTERLOT...
TO --

345
00:13:14,294 --> 00:13:16,063
HUH?
[ THUD! ]

346
00:13:16,096 --> 00:13:17,430
CANTERLOT?!

347
00:13:17,464 --> 00:13:18,966
OH, I AM SO ENVIOUS.

348
00:13:18,999 --> 00:13:21,168
THE GLAMOUR,
THE SOPHISTICATION.

349
00:13:21,201 --> 00:13:23,503
I'VE ALWAYS DREAMED
OF LIVING THERE.

350
00:13:23,536 --> 00:13:27,074
I CAN'T WAIT TO HEAR
ALL ABOUT IT.

351
00:13:27,107 --> 00:13:30,944
WE ARE GONNA BE THE BEST
OF FRIENDS, YOU AND I.

352
00:13:30,978 --> 00:13:33,580
EMERALDS?!
WHAT WAS I THINKING?

353
00:13:33,613 --> 00:13:35,548
LET ME GET YOU
SOME RUBIES.

354
00:13:35,582 --> 00:13:38,585
QUICK, BEFORE SHE DECIDES TO DYE
MY COAT A NEW COLOR.

355
00:13:38,618 --> 00:13:40,487
[ SIGHS ]

356
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:43,490
WASN'T SHE WONDERFUL?

357
00:13:43,523 --> 00:13:44,992
FOCUS, CASANOVA.

358
00:13:45,025 --> 00:13:46,226
WHAT'S NEXT
ON THE LIST?

359
00:13:46,259 --> 00:13:48,428
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
OH, UH, MUSIC.

360
00:13:48,461 --> 00:13:49,997
IT'S THE LAST ONE.

361
00:13:50,030 --> 00:13:53,033
[ BIRDS SINGING ]

362
00:14:01,274 --> 00:14:03,944
OH, MY.
UM, STOP, PLEASE, EVERYONE.

363
00:14:03,977 --> 00:14:06,213
UM...EXCUSE ME, SIR.

364
00:14:06,246 --> 00:14:07,180
I MEAN NO OFFENSE,

365
00:14:07,214 --> 00:14:11,184
BUT YOUR RHYTHM IS JUST
A TEENY, TINY BIT OFF.

366
00:14:11,218 --> 00:14:13,020
NOW FOLLOW ME, PLEASE.

367
00:14:13,053 --> 00:14:15,956
A-ONE, A-TWO,
A-ONE, TWO, THREE.

368
00:14:15,989 --> 00:14:18,025
Twilight Sparkle: HELLO!
[ GASPS ]

369
00:14:18,058 --> 00:14:19,927
OH, MY.
I'M SO SORRY.

370
00:14:19,927 --> 00:14:21,361
I DIDN'T MEAN TO FRIGHTEN
YOUR BIRDS.

371
00:14:21,394 --> 00:14:23,096
I'M JUST HERE TO CHECK UP
ON THE MUSIC,

372
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:25,232
AND IT SOUNDED BEAUTIFUL.

373
00:14:28,435 --> 00:14:31,071
[ SQUEAK! SQUEAK! SQUEAK! ]

374
00:14:31,104 --> 00:14:34,341
I'M TWILIGHT SPARKLE.

375
00:14:34,374 --> 00:14:36,143
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

376
00:14:36,176 --> 00:14:39,579
UM...I'M...[MUMBLES]

377
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:41,648
I'M SORRY.
WHAT WAS THAT?

378
00:14:41,681 --> 00:14:45,318
UM...MY NAME IS...
[MUMBLES]

379
00:14:45,352 --> 00:14:47,654
DIDN'T QUITE CATCH THAT.

380
00:14:47,687 --> 00:14:50,257
[ WHIMPERS ]

381
00:14:53,660 --> 00:14:57,364
WELL, UM, IT LOOKS LIKE
YOUR BIRDS ARE BACK.

382
00:14:57,397 --> 00:14:59,532
SO I GUESS
EVERYTHING'S IN ORDER.

383
00:14:59,566 --> 00:15:01,268
KEEP UP THE GOOD WORK.

384
00:15:01,301 --> 00:15:03,336
[ WHIMPERS ]

385
00:15:03,370 --> 00:15:05,172
OKAY.

386
00:15:06,306 --> 00:15:08,475
WELL, THAT WAS EASY.

387
00:15:08,508 --> 00:15:11,578
[ GASPS ]
A BABY DRAGON!

388
00:15:11,611 --> 00:15:15,048
OH, I'VE NEVER SEEN
A BABY DRAGON BEFORE.

389
00:15:15,082 --> 00:15:17,150
HE'S SO CUTE.

390
00:15:17,184 --> 00:15:19,052
WELL, WELL, WELL.

391
00:15:19,086 --> 00:15:20,988
OH, MY.
HE TALKS.

392
00:15:21,021 --> 00:15:23,056
I DIDN'T KNOW
DRAGONS COULD TALK.

393
00:15:23,090 --> 00:15:25,492
THAT'S JUST
SO INCREDIBLY WONDERFUL.

394
00:15:25,525 --> 00:15:28,128
I-I JUST DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

395
00:15:28,161 --> 00:15:29,062
[ TINKLE! ]

396
00:15:29,096 --> 00:15:30,998
WELL, IN THAT CASE,
WE BETTER BE GOING.

397
00:15:30,998 --> 00:15:32,365
WAIT, WAIT.

398
00:15:32,399 --> 00:15:33,433
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

399
00:15:33,466 --> 00:15:34,501
I'M SPIKE.

400
00:15:34,534 --> 00:15:37,037
HI, SPIKE.
I'M FLUTTERSHY.

401
00:15:37,070 --> 00:15:39,206
WOW, A TALKING DRAGON.

402
00:15:39,239 --> 00:15:41,074
AND WHAT DO DRAGONS
TALK ABOUT?

403
00:15:41,108 --> 00:15:42,675
WELL, WHAT DO YOU WANT
TO KNOW?

404
00:15:42,709 --> 00:15:45,612
ABSOLUTELY EVERYTHING.

405
00:15:45,645 --> 00:15:47,614
[ GROANS ]

406
00:15:47,647 --> 00:15:50,217
WELL, I STARTED OUT

407
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:52,619
AS A CUTE LITTLE
PURPLE-AND-GREEN EGG.

408
00:15:52,652 --> 00:15:56,523
AND THAT'S THE STORY
OF MY WHOLE ENTIRE LIFE...

409
00:15:56,556 --> 00:15:58,158
WELL, UP UNTIL TODAY.

410
00:15:58,191 --> 00:15:59,492
DO YOU WANT TO HEAR
ABOUT TODAY?

411
00:15:59,526 --> 00:16:01,361
OH, YES, PLEASE.

412
00:16:01,394 --> 00:16:02,362
WUH!

413
00:16:02,395 --> 00:16:03,630
I AM SO SORRY.

414
00:16:03,663 --> 00:16:05,498
HOW DID WE GET HERE
SO FAST?

415
00:16:05,532 --> 00:16:07,767
THIS IS WHERE I'M STAYING
WHILE IN PONYVILLE,

416
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:10,303
AND MY POOR BABY DRAGON
NEEDS HIS SLEEP.

417
00:16:10,337 --> 00:16:12,105
NO, I DON'T.
AAH!

418
00:16:12,139 --> 00:16:13,573
[ Baby talk ] AWW!
WOOK AT THAT.

419
00:16:13,606 --> 00:16:17,244
HE'S SO SWEEPY, HE CAN'T EVEN
KEEP HIS WITTLE BAWANCE.

420
00:16:17,277 --> 00:16:18,511
POOR THING.

421
00:16:18,545 --> 00:16:20,447
YOU SIMPLY MUST GET HIM
TO BED.

422
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:21,248
[ ZIP! ]

423
00:16:21,281 --> 00:16:23,216
YES, YES.
WE'LL GET RIGHT ON THAT.

424
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:24,251
WELL, GOOD NIGHT.

425
00:16:24,284 --> 00:16:25,485
[ SLAM! ]

426
00:16:25,518 --> 00:16:27,354
HUH. RUDE MUCH?

427
00:16:27,387 --> 00:16:29,589
SORRY, SPIKE, BUT I HAVE TO
CONVINCE THE PRINCESS

428
00:16:29,622 --> 00:16:31,224
THAT NIGHTMARE MOON
IS COMING,

429
00:16:31,258 --> 00:16:32,659
AND WE'RE RUNNING
OUT OF TIME.

430
00:16:32,692 --> 00:16:34,327
I JUST NEED TO BE ALONE
SO I CAN STUDY

431
00:16:34,361 --> 00:16:35,562
WITHOUT A BUNCH
OF CRAZY PONIES

432
00:16:35,595 --> 00:16:37,164
TRYING TO MAKE FRIENDS
ALL THE TIME.

433
00:16:37,197 --> 00:16:38,531
NOW, WHERE'S THE LIGHT?

434
00:16:38,565 --> 00:16:41,534
SURPRISE!
SURPRISE!
SURPRISE!

435
00:16:41,568 --> 00:16:42,802
[ HORN BLOWS ]

436
00:16:42,835 --> 00:16:44,071
[ GROANS ]

437
00:16:47,674 --> 00:16:49,076
SURPRISE!

438
00:16:49,076 --> 00:16:49,909
HI.
I'M PINKIE PIE.

439
00:16:49,942 --> 00:16:51,811
AND I THREW THIS PARTY
JUST FOR YOU.

440
00:16:51,844 --> 00:16:53,780
WERE YOU SURPRISED?
WERE YOU, WERE YOU?
HUH? HUH? HUH?

441
00:16:53,813 --> 00:16:55,448
VERY SURPRISED.

442
00:16:55,482 --> 00:16:57,384
LIBRARIES ARE SUPPOSED TO BE
QUIET.

443
00:16:57,417 --> 00:16:58,551
[ Chuckling ]
THAT'S SILLY.

444
00:16:58,585 --> 00:17:00,753
WHAT KIND OF WELCOME PARTY
WOULD THIS BE IF IT WERE QUIET?

445
00:17:00,787 --> 00:17:03,123
I MEAN, DUH!
BORING!

446
00:17:03,156 --> 00:17:04,824
YOU SEE, I SAW YOU WHEN YOU
FIRST GOT HERE, REMEMBER?

447
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:06,559
YOU WERE ALL, "HELLO."
AND I WAS ALL [GASPS]

448
00:17:06,593 --> 00:17:08,228
REMEMBER?
YOU SEE, I NEVER SAW YOU BEFORE.

449
00:17:08,261 --> 00:17:10,097
AND IF I NEVER SAW YOU BEFORE,
THAT MEANS YOU'RE NEW,

450
00:17:10,130 --> 00:17:13,100
'CAUSE I KNOW EVERYPONY, AND
I MEAN EVERYPONY, IN PONYVILLE.
[ GROANS ]

451
00:17:13,133 --> 00:17:14,734
AND IF YOU'RE NEW,
YOU HADN'T MET ANYONE YET.

452
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:16,703
AND IF YOU HAVEN'T MET
ANYONE YET, YOU MUST
NOT HAVE ANY FRIENDS.

453
00:17:16,736 --> 00:17:18,571
AND IF YOU DON'T HAVE
ANY FRIENDS, THEN
YOU MUST BE LONELY.

454
00:17:18,605 --> 00:17:20,640
AND THAT MADE ME SO SAD.
AND I HAD AN IDEA.

455
00:17:20,673 --> 00:17:22,375
AND THAT'S WHY I WENT
[GASPS]

456
00:17:22,409 --> 00:17:23,510
"I SHOULD THROW
A GREAT, BIG, GINORMOUS,

457
00:17:23,543 --> 00:17:25,445
SUPER-DUPER, SPECTACULAR
WELCOME PARTY

458
00:17:25,478 --> 00:17:27,347
AND INVITE EVERYONE
IN PONYVILLE."

459
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:29,649
SEE? AND NOW YOU HAVE
LOTS AND LOTS OF FRIENDS.

460
00:17:29,682 --> 00:17:30,583
[ POP! ]

461
00:17:30,617 --> 00:17:34,754
Applejack: ARE YOU ALL RIGHT,
SUGAR CUBE?

462
00:17:34,787 --> 00:17:36,656
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

463
00:17:36,689 --> 00:17:39,726
AWW!
SHE'S SO HAPPY, SHE'S CRYING.

464
00:17:42,295 --> 00:17:44,397
HOT SAUCE.

465
00:17:44,431 --> 00:17:45,632
OOH.

466
00:17:47,134 --> 00:17:50,303
[ Muffled ] WHAT?
THIS IS GOOD.

467
00:17:50,337 --> 00:17:53,240
[ DANCE MUSIC PLAYING ]

468
00:17:53,273 --> 00:17:55,875
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

469
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:58,278
UGH.
Spike: HEY, TWILIGHT,

470
00:17:58,311 --> 00:18:00,780
PINKIE PIE'S STARTING
"PIN THE TAIL ON THE PONY."

471
00:18:00,813 --> 00:18:02,515
WANT TO PLAY?
NO!

472
00:18:02,549 --> 00:18:05,285
ALL THE PONIES IN THIS TOWN
ARE CRAZY!

473
00:18:05,318 --> 00:18:06,886
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT TIME IT IS?

474
00:18:06,919 --> 00:18:09,256
IT'S THE EVE
OF THE SUMMER SUN CELEBRATION.

475
00:18:09,289 --> 00:18:10,223
EVERYPONY HAS TO STAY UP,

476
00:18:10,257 --> 00:18:12,525
OR THEY'LL MISS
THE PRINCESS RAISE THE SUN.

477
00:18:12,559 --> 00:18:14,661
YOU REALLY SHOULD LIGHTEN UP,
TWILIGHT.

478
00:18:14,694 --> 00:18:16,196
IT'S A PARTY.

479
00:18:16,229 --> 00:18:19,166
[ MUMBLING ]

480
00:18:19,166 --> 00:18:20,900
UGH! HERE, I THOUGHT
I'D HAVE TIME

481
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:24,171
TO LEARN MORE ABOUT THE ELEMENTS
OF HARMONY, BUT SILLY ME.

482
00:18:24,171 --> 00:18:25,872
ALL THIS RIDICULOUS
FRIEND-MAKING

483
00:18:25,905 --> 00:18:27,240
HAS KEPT ME FROM IT.

484
00:18:29,409 --> 00:18:33,513
LEGEND HAS IT THAT ON THE
LONGEST DAY OF THE 1,000th YEAR,

485
00:18:33,546 --> 00:18:35,482
THE STARS WILL AID
IN HER ESCAPE,

486
00:18:35,515 --> 00:18:37,784
AND SHE WILL BRING ABOUT
EVERLASTING NIGHT.

487
00:18:37,817 --> 00:18:40,920
I HOPE THE PRINCESS WAS RIGHT.

488
00:18:40,953 --> 00:18:43,490
I HOPE IT REALLY IS
JUST AN OLD PONY TALE.

489
00:18:43,523 --> 00:18:44,657
Spike:
COME ON, TWILIGHT!

490
00:18:44,691 --> 00:18:46,593
IT'S TIME TO WATCH
THE SUN RISE.

491
00:18:46,626 --> 00:18:48,395
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

492
00:18:54,601 --> 00:18:55,668
ISN'T THIS EXCITING?

493
00:18:55,702 --> 00:18:56,803
ARE YOU EXCITED?
'CAUSE I'M EXCITED.

494
00:18:56,836 --> 00:18:58,004
I'VE NEVER BEEN
SO EXCITED.

495
00:18:58,037 --> 00:19:00,340
WELL, EXCEPT FOR THE TIME THAT I
SAW YOU WALKING INTO TOWN,

496
00:19:00,373 --> 00:19:01,274
AND I WENT [GASPS]

497
00:19:01,308 --> 00:19:03,276
BUT, I MEAN, REALLY,
WHO CAN TOP THAT?

498
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:04,311
[ BIRDS SINGING ]

499
00:19:09,816 --> 00:19:13,920
FILLIES AND GENTLECOLTS,
AS MAYOR OF PONYVILLE,

500
00:19:13,953 --> 00:19:16,723
IT IS MY GREAT PLEASURE
TO ANNOUNCE THE BEGINNING

501
00:19:16,756 --> 00:19:19,292
OF THE SUMMER SUN
CELEBRATION.

502
00:19:19,326 --> 00:19:20,727
[ ALL CHEERING ]

503
00:19:22,829 --> 00:19:24,964
IN JUST A FEW MOMENTS,
OUR TOWN

504
00:19:24,997 --> 00:19:27,300
WILL WITNESS
THE MAGIC OF THE SUNRISE

505
00:19:27,334 --> 00:19:31,371
AND CELEBRATE THIS,
THE LONGEST DAY OF THE YEAR.

506
00:19:31,404 --> 00:19:34,441
AND NOW, IT IS MY GREAT HONOR
TO INTRODUCE TO YOU

507
00:19:34,474 --> 00:19:35,975
THE RULER OF OUR LAND,

508
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:38,478
THE VERY PONY WHO GIVES US
THE SUN AND THE MOON

509
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:39,646
EACH AND EVERY DAY,

510
00:19:39,679 --> 00:19:41,614
THE GOOD, THE WISE,

511
00:19:41,648 --> 00:19:44,251
THE BRINGER OF HARMONY
TO ALL OF EQUESTRIA...

512
00:19:44,284 --> 00:19:45,785
READY?

513
00:19:45,818 --> 00:19:47,587
...PRINCESS CELESTIA!

514
00:19:47,620 --> 00:19:50,323
[ BIRDS SINGING ]

515
00:19:50,357 --> 00:19:52,792
HUH?

516
00:19:52,825 --> 00:19:54,727
THIS CAN'T BE GOOD.

517
00:19:54,761 --> 00:19:56,996
[ CROWD MURMURING ]
REMAIN CALM, EVERYPONY.

518
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:58,965
THERE MUST BE
A REASONABLE EXPLANATION.

519
00:19:58,998 --> 00:20:01,534
OOH, OOH!
I LOVE GUESSING GAMES.

520
00:20:01,568 --> 00:20:02,935
IS SHE HIDING?

521
00:20:02,969 --> 00:20:04,904
SHE'S GONE!

522
00:20:04,937 --> 00:20:07,674
[ ALL GASP ]

523
00:20:07,707 --> 00:20:10,877
OOH, SHE'S GOOD.

524
00:20:10,910 --> 00:20:12,011
AAH!

525
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:13,713
[ ALL GASP ]

526
00:20:13,746 --> 00:20:15,948
OH, NO.

527
00:20:17,917 --> 00:20:19,952
NIGHTMARE MOON.

528
00:20:19,986 --> 00:20:21,654
OH!

529
00:20:21,688 --> 00:20:24,424
OH, MY BELOVED SUBJECTS.

530
00:20:24,457 --> 00:20:25,958
IT'S BEEN SO LONG

531
00:20:25,992 --> 00:20:29,729
SINCE I'VE SEEN YOUR PRECIOUS
LITTLE SUN-LOVING FACES.

532
00:20:29,762 --> 00:20:31,831
WHAT DID YOU DO
WITH OUR PRINCESS?

533
00:20:31,864 --> 00:20:33,833
SLOW DOWN, NELLY.

534
00:20:33,866 --> 00:20:36,636
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]
WHY?

535
00:20:36,669 --> 00:20:38,805
AM I NOT ROYAL ENOUGH
FOR YOU?

536
00:20:38,838 --> 00:20:40,473
DON'T YOU KNOW WHO I AM?

537
00:20:40,507 --> 00:20:42,275
OOH, OOH!
MORE GUESSING GAMES.

538
00:20:42,309 --> 00:20:43,543
UM, HOKEY SMOKES.

539
00:20:43,576 --> 00:20:45,412
HOW ABOUT QUEEN MEANIE?

540
00:20:45,445 --> 00:20:47,280
NO.
BLACK SNOOTY, BLACK SNOOTY!

541
00:20:47,314 --> 00:20:49,449
[ MUFFLED SPEAKING ]

542
00:20:49,482 --> 00:20:51,384
DOES MY CROWN
NO LONGER COUNT

543
00:20:51,418 --> 00:20:54,887
NOW THAT I HAVE BEEN IMPRISONED
FOR 1,000 YEARS?

544
00:20:54,921 --> 00:20:56,623
DID YOU NOT RECALL
THE LEGEND?

545
00:20:56,656 --> 00:20:58,591
DID YOU NOT SEE
THE SIGNS?

546
00:20:58,625 --> 00:21:00,993
I DID,
AND I KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

547
00:21:01,027 --> 00:21:04,497
YOU'RE THE MARE IN THE MOON,
NIGHTMARE MOON.

548
00:21:04,531 --> 00:21:05,798
[ ALL GASP ]

549
00:21:05,832 --> 00:21:07,667
WELL, WELL, WELL.

550
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:09,736
SOMEPONY
WHO REMEMBERS ME.

551
00:21:09,769 --> 00:21:11,838
THEN YOU ALSO KNOW
WHY I'M HERE.

552
00:21:11,871 --> 00:21:14,441
YOU'RE HERE TO...TO...

553
00:21:14,474 --> 00:21:15,742
[ GULPS ]

554
00:21:15,775 --> 00:21:17,076
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

555
00:21:17,109 --> 00:21:19,346
REMEMBER THIS DAY,
LITTLE PONIES,

556
00:21:19,346 --> 00:21:20,947
FOR IT WAS YOUR LAST.

557
00:21:20,980 --> 00:21:26,085
FROM THIS MOMENT FORTH,
THE NIGHT WILL LAST FOREVER!

558
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:27,520
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

559
00:21:27,554 --> 00:21:29,055
[ THUNDER CRASHING ]

560
00:21:36,996 --> 00:21:39,632
* MY LITTLE PONY

561
00:21:41,668 --> 00:21:44,003
* MY LITTLE PONY

562
00:21:54,447 --> 00:21:56,849
* MY LITTLE PONY

563
00:21:56,883 --> 00:22:03,890
* FRIENDS

